Defendant Katie L Medved in court, in custody, with attorney Katie B. Bricco.   Pablo Galaviz and law intern Jack Pitzo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State presents argument.  Defense counsel presents argument.  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED SENTENCE of: 

COUNT 1:  

7 YEARS IMPRISONMENT CONSECUTIVE
  -  3 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  4 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

COUNT 2:

2 YEARS IMPRISONMENT Concurrent to Count 1
  - 1 YEAR OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  - 1 YEAR OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*No contact with:  Walgreens on Sunset, Anne B., ValuCare on South Grand, Randy D. or co-actors.

RESTITUTION (as previously ordered):  $500.00 to ValuCare and $1,857.99 to Pharmacy Mutual Insurance.  JOINT AND SEVERAL WITH CO-ACTORS (to be paid at the rate of $50.00 per month commencing the 6th month of supervision);

COURT COSTS (as previously ordered):  $268.00 as to each count (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);

DNA SURCHARGE (as previously ordered):  $250.00 as to each count

DRGOD (as previously ordered):  $10.00 as to Count 1 (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);

Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
